2.4 Defining offsite impacts - 68.30 / 68.33



According to the model, offsite impacts will differ for a VCE and VCF and be limited to their respective impact radius.  There are no public receptors such as schools, hospitals, prisons, arenas, or major commercial developments within the affected area.  There is an industrial facility to the northwest. 



There are no natural areas such as state parks, forests, or monuments; officially designated wildlife sanctuaries, preserves, refuges, or areas; or federal wilderness areas within the affected area.  A portion of the Allegheny National Forest does exist within the area for a VCE. 







2.5 Passive Mitigation



There are no structures that can contain and mitigate the worst-case release scenario.







2.6 Documentation - 68.39



Documentation of the following is part of the RMP kept on-site.



     a)  For the worst-case scenario:

          - a description of the vessel or pipeline selected as a worst-case release;

          - assumptions, input parameters used, and the rationale for selection;

          - listed in section 2.2 of this document, the selection of the scenario corresponds with the requirements detailed in 40 CFR 68.25(e)(1);



     b)  For the alternative release scenarios:

          - a description of the vessel or pipeline selected as an alternative release;

          - assumptions, input parameters used, and the rationale for selection;

          - listed in section 2.3 of this document, the selection of the scenarios corresponds with the requirements detailed in 40 CFR 68.28(b)(2)(ii); 



     c)  Documentation of estimated quantity released, release rate, and duration of release:

          - listed in section 2.2 and 2.3 of this document;



     d)  Methodology used t

